get_user_photos(user_id: int, top: int = None, **params: Unpack[ParamsPhotosGet]) → List[VkPhoto][source]

Returns user photos

See https://dev.vk.com/ru/method/photos.get

Parameters:

  • user_id – ID of VK user to get photos of.

  • top – (optional) If set, that many photos will be returned, sorted by count of likes.

  • params – (optional) Additional method parameters. Default value for album_id is “profile”. If top is not None, then extended is always 1 and count is always 1000.

Returns:

Parsed endpoint response containing photos information.

Raises:

VKError – If VK API responded with an error.
